<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-02-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-02-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="725" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-02-22"><hi rend="italic">February 22,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Choate reports that the foreign office had not, until his inquiry,
                            learned of the seizure of the <hi rend="italic">Sabine</hi>, but that
                            inquiries will at once be instituted and the results reported to him. He
                            requests to be advised of date and place of seizure and present
                            whereabouts of the vessel.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>